Terrorists are said to have attacked Ukuru Village in Bobi District, Mariga Local Government Area of Niger State on Wednesday, and killed a yet-to-be-specified number of people with houses set ablaze.  Our correspondent gathered that the terrorists also burnt vehicles and shops while on the rampage. A large number of villagers were also said to have been abducted by the terrorists. It was gathered that the gunmen invaded the community in very large numbers riding on motorcycles, all of them carrying AK-47 rifles.   Source By Unini Chioma Residents of 65 communities in Niger State have resorted to negotiating and signing a peace deal with Boko Haram to avoid future raids by the insurgents, FIJ reports. This development came few days after the terror group displaced over 5,000 villagers from their ancestral homes in Shiroro… In "Top Stories" •Boko Haram terrorists By ABDULAZIZ ABDULAZIZ ABUJA - Insurgent groups; Jama’atu Ahlul Sunnah lid Da’awatu wal Jihad (JAS, better known as Boko Haram), Islamic State in West Africa Province (ISWAP) and Jama’atu Ansarul Muslimina fii Biladis Sudan (Vanguard for the Protection of Muslims in Black Africa, also known as Ansaru) are… In "Top Stories" Retired generals and former military head of states are alarmed that Boko Haram terrorists appeared to be  winning in their war against Nigeria. According to reports from Tribune, one of the retired Generals, former President Olusegun Obasanjo, who visited Ibadan, the Oyo State capital, on Friday, was said to have voiced… In "News"